            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-40973",
              "name": "LanguageSpecificPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Spring Boot: Spring Boot: Arbitrary Code Execution and Session Hijacking via predictable temporary directory"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "A local attacker on the same host as the application may be able to take control of the directory used by `ApplicationTemp`. When `server.servlet.session.persistent` is set to `true` and the attack persists across application restarts, this may allow the attacker to read session information and hijack authenticated users or deploy a gadget chain and execute code as the application's user.\n\nAffected: Spring Boot 4.0.0–4.0.5 (fix 4.0.6), 3.5.0–3.5.13 (fix 3.5.14), 3.4.0–3.4.15 (fix 3.4.16), 3.3.0–3.3.18 (fix 3.3.19), 2.7.0–2.7.32 (fix 2.7.33); predictable temp directory / `ApplicationTemp` ownership verification. Versions that are no longer supported are also affected per vendor advisory."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-40973",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2026-40973\nSeverity: HIGH\nPackage: org.springframework.boot:spring-boot\nFixed Version: 4.0.6, 3.5.14\nLink: [CVE-2026-40973](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-40973)\nA local attacker on the same host as the application may be able to take control of the directory used by `ApplicationTemp`. When `server.servlet.session.persistent` is set to `true` and the attack persists across application restarts, this may allow the attacker to read session information and hijack authenticated users or deploy a gadget chain and execute code as the application's user.\n\nAffected: Spring Boot 4.0.0–4.0.5 (fix 4.0.6), 3.5.0–3.5.13 (fix 3.5.14), 3.4.0–3.4.15 (fix 3.4.16), 3.3.0–3.3.18 (fix 3.3.19), 2.7.0–2.7.32 (fix 2.7.33); predictable temp directory / `ApplicationTemp` ownership verification. Versions that are no longer supported are also affected per vendor advisory.",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2026-40973**\n| Severity | Package | Fixed Version | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n|HIGH|org.springframework.boot:spring-boot|4.0.6, 3.5.14|[CVE-2026-40973](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-40973)|\n\nA local attacker on the same host as the application may be able to take control of the directory used by `ApplicationTemp`. When `server.servlet.session.persistent` is set to `true` and the attack persists across application restarts, this may allow the attacker to read session information and hijack authenticated users or deploy a gadget chain and execute code as the application's user.\n\nAffected: Spring Boot 4.0.0–4.0.5 (fix 4.0.6), 3.5.0–3.5.13 (fix 3.5.14), 3.4.0–3.4.15 (fix 3.4.16), 3.3.0–3.3.18 (fix 3.3.19), 2.7.0–2.7.32 (fix 2.7.33); predictable temp directory / `ApplicationTemp` ownership verification. Versions that are no longer supported are also affected per vendor advisory."
              },
