              "id": "CVE-2026-22746",
              "name": "LanguageSpecificPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Spring Security: Spring Security: Timing attack defense bypass allows information disclosure"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Vulnerability in Spring Spring Security. If an application is using the UserDetails#isEnabled, #isAccountNonExpired, or #isAccountNonLocked user attributes, to enable, expire, or lock users, then DaoAuthenticationProvider's timing attack defense can be bypassed for users who are disabled, expired, or locked.This issue affects Spring Security: from 5.7.0 through 5.7.22, from 5.8.0 through 5.8.24, from 6.3.0 through 6.3.15, from 6.5.0 through 6.5.9, from 7.0.0 through 7.0.4."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "note"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-22746",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2026-22746\nSeverity: LOW\nPackage: org.springframework.security:spring-security-core\nFixed Version: 6.5.10, 7.0.5\nLink: [CVE-2026-22746](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-22746)\nVulnerability in Spring Spring Security. If an application is using the UserDetails#isEnabled, #isAccountNonExpired, or #isAccountNonLocked user attributes, to enable, expire, or lock users, then DaoAuthenticationProvider's timing attack defense can be bypassed for users who are disabled, expired, or locked.This issue affects Spring Security: from 5.7.0 through 5.7.22, from 5.8.0 through 5.8.24, from 6.3.0 through 6.3.15, from 6.5.0 through 6.5.9, from 7.0.0 through 7.0.4.",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2026-22746**\n| Severity | Package | Fixed Version | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n|LOW|org.springframework.security:spring-security-core|6.5.10, 7.0.5|[CVE-2026-22746](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-22746)|\n\nVulnerability in Spring Spring Security. If an application is using the UserDetails#isEnabled, #isAccountNonExpired, or #isAccountNonLocked user attributes, to enable, expire, or lock users, then DaoAuthenticationProvider's timing attack defense can be bypassed for users who are disabled, expired, or locked.This issue affects Spring Security: from 5.7.0 through 5.7.22, from 5.8.0 through 5.8.24, from 6.3.0 through 6.3.15, from 6.5.0 through 6.5.9, from 7.0.0 through 7.0.4."
